author: Danielle Berjikian
description:
I know you didn’t need any more evidence to prove the left despises women, but here you go!

According to Michelle Obama, producing life is the “least important thing” a woman can do. And by her admission, she has proved how much the left despises humanity.

Tell me you’re part of the party that hates women without telling me you’re part of the party that hates women: Michelle will go first.


According to Michelle Obama, the “least important thing” about a woman’s reproductive system is that “it produces life.”pic.twitter.com/zxbqklcFXX
— Dinesh D'Souza (@DineshDSouza)
title: Michelle Obama claims a woman’s reproductive system isn’t for… reproducing. Really?

author: Danielle Berjikian
description:
You can't participate in one of the biggest cover-ups in American history and then expect people to believe you were completely unaware, especially after pushing that narrative for over five years.

In other words, you can’t have your cake and eat it too. That’s why it was incredibly foolish for CNN’s Jake Tapper to write a book about his sudden “realization” that Biden was, is, and always has been a sleeping potato. Because if I knew, and you knew, and you knew I knew—then he definitely knew.

So, he has no one to blame but himself for his show’s record-low ratings.


LOL. CNN's Jake Tapper has reportedly lost 25% of his viewers in one year, achieving his lowest ratings since 2015, despite his recent attempt to convince people that he wasn't part
title: Jake Tapper's book tour makes more sense when you see how RECORD LOW his ratings are

author: Brodigan
description:
There's never a bad time to defecate on how legacy media and all who work in it are a failure of an institution and sucks at life. The latest is Vice President JD Vance, by comparing it to another failing institution... Congress.

It was part of a wide-ranging interview. These bars, discussing the legal brouhaha (if I may invoke a little French) surrounding Trump's use of an emergency declaration to push tariffs, are important. Vance's point about having to rely on other countries for critical supplies (such as relying on China to cure us of the China Virus) is a point that isn't being made loudly enough. And one that, dare I say, is more effective than 3 AM social media rants.

WATCH: JD Vance says America is in an emergency and it’s time to bring industry back home
title: JD Vance REVELS in how bad legacy media fails at life these days: "It's almost a skill in and of itself"

author: Brodigan
description:
We interrupt our coverage of Trump Tariffs and Jake Tapper dressing like a hot dog and wondering "who did this?" to bring you the odds-on favorite to win 2025's Louder with Crowder Dot Com Website Man of the Year. A dude bro from down under woke up one morning and decided what We The Content needed was a guy who wakes up and fights a different follower every day until one of them sleeps him. And you know what? Mans is right!

I don't know who Chrogman is, but he has just replaced Angus Young and Bandit Heeler as our favorite Australian. Or, our favorite male Aussie Aussie Aussie (Oi Oi Oi). AEW's Harley Cameron still tops the list overall.
title: Instagram bro goes viral fighting his followers until he "gets knocked the f*** out" and he's the hero we all need
